Program: The History Hour
Title: The University of Texas Shooting
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0430fhr
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 8 Aug 2016
On 1 August 1966, student Charles Whitman shot dead 14 people and injured another 32 in America's first mass shooting at a university. Plus, the oldest arts festival in the Middle East; how President Reagan smashed the power of the trade unions; and meeting JD Salinger, the reclusive author of "The Catcher in the Rye". PHOTO: Associated Press. Show less